<dl id="n56179c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n56" href="#n56179c">N56 (VI.B.41)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n56all.htm#n56179c"> 179(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> the Lous, the / Gryffs &amp; the / Wilde mann <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n56179c"><li>FW 358.22f </li><li><a href="../../flex/mf/lexmf.htm#n56179c">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/mf/l39mf.htm#n56179c">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n56179c">MS BL 47480-218v</ms> </li><li>JJA 55:420 <a name="mfd5y" href="../../FF/fdra/mda.htm#mfd5y">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/mf/mfd5.htm#n56179c">Draft: II.3&sect;6.5</a>+ </li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: At the annual festival in Basel, two figures (also names of Basel river-ferries), <i>der wilde Mann</i> and <i>Vogel Gryff</i> arrive on a float. A third ferry is named &apos;Leu&apos; [Lion]. French <i>loup</i>: wolf. Griffin: mythological beast, with the body of a lion and an eagle&apos;s beak and wings. Wild man. </mm> </dd></dl>
